  "prompt": "Are there any scholarships in MBBS program in Germany for Pakistani students?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several scholarships available for Pakistani students interested in pursuing an MBBS program in Germany. Here are some options to consider:\n\n1. **DAAD Scholarships**: The German Academic Exchange Service (DAAD) offers a variety of scholarships for international students, including those from Pakistan. These scholarships can help cover living expenses, travel costs, and tuition fees.\n\n2. **Deutschlandstipendium**: This merit-based scholarship provides financial support to talented students from all over the world, including Pakistan. It encourages academic excellence and can be applied for through the respective universities.\n\n3. **University-Specific Scholarships**: Many German universities offer their own scholarships to international students, including those in medical programs. For instance, universities like Heidelberg University, Charit\u00e9 \u2013 Universit\u00e4tsmedizin Berlin, and others might have specific funds or grants for international students.\n\n4. **Erasmus+ Program**: While traditionally focused on European students, this program also has possibilities for non-European students. It provides scholarships for study abroad, including within Germany.\n\n5. **Private and Non-Governmental Scholarships**: Various organizations and foundations provide scholarships for international students who want to study in Germany. Examples include the Friedrich Ebert Stiftung, Heinrich B\u00f6ll Foundation, and Konrad Adenauer Stiftung.\n\nPakistani students should check the specific eligibility criteria and application procedures for each scholarship. It's also recommended to directly contact the universities in Germany and inquire about available scholarships for MBBS programs. Additionally, consulting with educational consultants specializing in study abroad programs can provide more personalized guidance.",
